OL,7,F"Mr Fox did not attempt to show these
OL,8,Fallegations were true, and he was not
OL,9,Fable to bring himself on the facts
OL,10,Fwithin the terms of any other defence
OL,11,Frecognised in law."
OL,13,FDuring a trial in London in November,
OL,14,FMr Fox was described as an alleged
OL,15,F"intelligent racist with an agenda".
OL,17,FLorna Skinner KC, representing Mr
OL,18,FBlake, Mr Seymour and Ms Thorp, said
OL,19,Fthe trio "honestly believed, and
OL,20,Fcontinue honestly to believe, that Mr
OL,21,FFox is a racist".
