OL,7,FHe continued: "Racism as a term is
OL,8,Fused just as a point of disagreement,
OL,9,Fand a point of 'I don't like you,
OL,10,Ftherefore you're a racist'.
OL,12,F"This is a great, wonderful country
OL,13,Fand I admire and I respect this
OL,14,Fcountry, and I fight for it and I
OL,15,Ffight for my children and I fight for
OL,16,Feverybody else out there who doesn't
OL,17,Fhave my platform who gets called these
OL,18,Fvicious slurs, and I just want a
OL,19,Fdefinition of the word."
